{"title":"Fabian Kalleitner","markdown":{"yaml":{"title":""},"headingText":"Fabian Kalleitner","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n:::{.column-page}\n\n<center>\n![](assets/profile.jpg){width=200px style=\"border-radius: 50%;\"}\n\n\n**Postdoctoral Researcher**  \nChair of Sociology and Empirical Social Research (LS4)\nDepartment of Sociology  \nLMU Munich\n</center>\n\n## Hi!  {.no-border}\nI am a Postdoctoral Researcher at the [Chair of Sociology and Empirical Social Research (LS4)](https://www.soziologie.lmu.de/en/our-department/faculty-and-staff/contact-page/fabian-kalleitner-e069e205.html), LMU Munich. My research interests include tax preferences, biased perceptions, fairness attitudes, and work values. To gather insights in these topics I combine theories and insights of sociology, economics, and psychology using various methodological approaches (i.e. panel surveys, multilevel analyses, survey/field/laboratory experiments) and estimation strategies.\n\nYou can contact me per email using [fabian.kalleitner@lmu.de](mailto:fabian.kalleitner@lmu.de).\n\n[Curriculum Vitae](https://syncandshare.lrz.de/dl/fi8HMRufYxqLvPfidtaNit/CV_Fabian_Kalleitner_eng.pdf?inline&skipCounter=true)\n\n<center>\n\n<a href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1196-824X\" class=\"btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm\">{{< ai orcid >}} ORCID</a>\n<a href=\"https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Fabian-Kalleitner\" class=\"btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm\">{{< ai researchgate >}} ResearchGate</a>\n<a href=\"https://scholar.google.at/citations?user=NoQflXIAAAAJ\" class=\"btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm\">{{< ai google-scholar >}} Google Scholar</a>\n<a href=\"https://bsky.app/profile/kalf.bsky.social\" class=\"btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm\"><i class=\"bi bi-bluesky\"></i> Bluesky</a>\n</center>\n\n\n---\n\n:::{.columns}\n:::{.column width=\"48%\"}\n\n### Education\n\n<ul style=\"list-style: none; padding-left: 1.5em;\">\n<li style=\"text-indent: -1.5em; padding-left: 1.5em;\"><i class=\"bi bi-mortarboard-fill\"></i> **PhD in Sociology** (2023)<br>University of Vienna</li>\n<li style=\"text-indent: -1.5em; padding-left: 1.5em;\"><i class=\"bi bi-mortarboard-fill\"></i> **MA in Sociology** (2017)<br>University of Vienna</li>\n<li style=\"text-indent: -1.5em; padding-left: 1.5em;\"><i class=\"bi bi-mortarboard-fill\"></i> **BA in History** (2015)<br>University of Vienna</li>\n<li style=\"text-indent: -1.5em; padding-left: 1.5em;\"><i class=\"bi bi-mortarboard-fill\"></i> **BA in Political Science** (2014)<br>University of Vienna</li>\n</ul>\n\n:::\n\n:::{.column width=\"4%\"}\n:::\n\n:::{.column width=\"48%\"}\n\n### Research Interests\n\n- Economic & social inequality\n- Quantitative methods\n- Survey research methodology\n- Tax and redistribution preferences\n- Work values\n\n:::\n:::\n\n:::","srcMarkdownNoYaml":"\n\n:::{.column-page}\n\n<center>\n![](assets/profile.jpg){width=200px style=\"border-radius: 50%;\"}\n\n# Fabian Kalleitner\n\n**Postdoctoral Researcher**  \nChair of Sociology and Empirical Social Research (LS4)\nDepartment of Sociology  \nLMU Munich\n</center>\n\n## Hi!  {.no-border}\nI am a Postdoctoral Researcher at the [Chair of Sociology and Empirical Social Research (LS4)](https://www.soziologie.lmu.de/en/our-department/faculty-and-staff/contact-page/fabian-kalleitner-e069e205.html), LMU Munich. My research interests include tax preferences, biased perceptions, fairness attitudes, and work values. To gather insights in these topics I combine theories and insights of sociology, economics, and psychology using various methodological approaches (i.e. panel surveys, multilevel analyses, survey/field/laboratory experiments) and estimation strategies.\n\nYou can contact me per email using [fabian.kalleitner@lmu.de](mailto:fabian.kalleitner@lmu.de).\n\n[Curriculum Vitae](https://syncandshare.lrz.de/dl/fi8HMRufYxqLvPfidtaNit/CV_Fabian_Kalleitner_eng.pdf?inline&skipCounter=true)\n\n<center>\n\n<a href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1196-824X\" class=\"btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm\">{{< ai orcid >}} ORCID</a>\n<a href=\"https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Fabian-Kalleitner\" class=\"btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm\">{{< ai researchgate >}} ResearchGate</a>\n<a href=\"https://scholar.google.at/citations?user=NoQflXIAAAAJ\" class=\"btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm\">{{< ai google-scholar >}} Google Scholar</a>\n<a href=\"https://bsky.app/profile/kalf.bsky.social\" class=\"btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm\"><i class=\"bi bi-bluesky\"></i> Bluesky</a>\n</center>\n\n\n---\n\n:::{.columns}\n:::{.column width=\"48%\"}\n\n### Education\n\n<ul style=\"list-style: none; padding-left: 1.5em;\">\n<li style=\"text-indent: -1.5em; padding-left: 1.5em;\"><i class=\"bi bi-mortarboard-fill\"></i> **PhD in Sociology** (2023)<br>University of Vienna</li>\n<li style=\"text-indent: -1.5em; padding-left: 1.5em;\"><i class=\"bi bi-mortarboard-fill\"></i> **MA in Sociology** (2017)<br>University of Vienna</li>\n<li style=\"text-indent: -1.5em; padding-left: 1.5em;\"><i class=\"bi bi-mortarboard-fill\"></i> **BA in History** (2015)<br>University of Vienna</li>\n<li style=\"text-indent: -1.5em; padding-left: 1.5em;\"><i class=\"bi bi-mortarboard-fill\"></i> **BA in Political Science** (2014)<br>University of Vienna</li>\n</ul>\n\n:::\n\n:::{.column width=\"4%\"}\n:::\n\n:::{.column width=\"48%\"}\n\n### Research Interests\n\n- Economic & social inequality\n- Quantitative methods\n- Survey research methodology\n- Tax and redistribution preferences\n- Work values\n\n:::\n:::\n\n:::"},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"